OL,7,FAngel didn't know what had hit her when
OL,8,Fshe got Covid last summer. Bed-bound
OL,9,Ffor three months, she relied on her
OL,10,Fhusband to do everything for her
OL,11,Fincluding fetching a bed pan.
OL,13,FDiagnosed with a long-haul form of the
OL,14,Fdisease and left struggling with
OL,15,Ffatigue and breathlessness, but
OL,16,Fdesperately needing an income, she
OL,17,Fattempted a phased return to her job on
OL,18,Fa hospital ward as a health care
OL,19,Fassistant in December. But it didn't go
OL,20,Fto plan.
OL,3,C'I'm an NHS worker with long Covid ` I
